What is Apex ?

Apex is a true Node as a Service (NaaS) protocol built on the Avalanche blockchain. Apex is dedicated to empowering Web 3.0 infrastructure through our nodes operating across a variety of blockchains. Apex deploys nodes for a wide range of blockchains and empowers these networks by increasing the decentralization and security of these blockchains including Arweave, Avalanche, Ethereum, and the Bitcoin Lightning Network. With our corporate headquarters located in Dubai, team and node infrastructure spanning the globe, Apex is destined to become the very fabric that underpins the new frontier that is Web 3.0.

How it works ?

In addition to our hardware nodes that support multiple blockchains, investors in the apex protocol can create an onchain node that provides investors passive income. To create an onchain node, you purchase 10 Apex tokens, enter the Apex dapp and click the create node button. Creating a node costs 10 apex tokens.

Reward Pool

7 of those 10 tokens used for node creation are returned to the rewards pool, 2 tokens are added to the Apex treasury and node operations fund, and 1 token is added to the liquidity pool. Node holders are paid .12 Apex tokens per day. These ratios of this model from Node Creation can change depending on market conditions.

Our Vision

Our team has been focused on developing partnerships with other projects in the web 3.0 space, as well as expanding cutting-edge use cases for both our nodes and the Apex token itself. Apex Chain will leverage our decentralized infrastructure to support an EVM capable of eliminating congestion from other EVM networks. Prior to the deployment of Apex Chain our team is building an entire ecosystem around Apex including a Decentralized Exchange (DEX), Autocompounder, and Lending platform. These platforms will increase demand for Apex tokens as well as provide an additional source of funding for the Apex Reserve Pool
